		<category name="Gear Overhaul 1.35">
			<comment>The Gear Overhaul is a several-month joint venture between Orudeon, AngrierPat, the_Nocturni, Zububu, LightChaosman, Mike, FromDarkHell et al.</comment>
			<comment>This mod extensively tweaks or overhauls (almost) every brand in the game to improve competitiveness of low-performing items or brands, as well as create sensible or synergistic changes.</comment>
			<comment>Overall, your gun choice, accessory choice, and even shield choice should matter a little bit less.</comment>
			<comment>This mod requires BLCMM to function correctly.</comment>
			<category name="Required Code">
				<code profiles="default">set WeaponPartDefinition'GD_Sage_Weapons.Pistols.Pistol_Barrel_Jakobs_Rex' ExternalAttributeEffects ((AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.GameplayAttributes.PlayerCriticalHitBonus',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.500000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=None,ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=0.000000)))</code>

					<category name="Aaron's Sniper Regen Replaces the Accuracy Accessory">
						<comment>########</comment>
						<comment>By Aaron0000</comment>
						<comment>Replaces the accuracy accessory of Sniper Rifles. Changes it to slowly regenerate ammo instead of increasing accuracy.</comment>

			<category name="Another Spiker Mod V1.0b by Orudeon">
				<comment>Redesigns Spikers into hand-held micro-rocket launchers. All spikers deal heavily increased damage, explode sooner, and now deal your choice of Reaper, Grenade, or Rocket (vanilla) splash.</comment>
				<comment>Bandit, Dahl, and Vladof Spikers have higher recoil, higher burst delay, and lower fire rate respectively to keep them in line with other brands while retaining their brand signature.</comment>
				<comment>Maliwan spikers have massively increased elemental chance and damage at the expense of lower DPS.</comment>
				<comment>A very special thank you to LightChaosman for coding the zero-delay detonation code.</comment>
				<comment>You must install this with LightChaosman's BLCMM or manually merge the hotfixes at the end of the document. Includes Jakobs and Torgue E-Tech compatibility baseline.</comment>
				<category name="Main Code">

			<category name="Bayonet Enhancements V1.4 by Orudeon">
				<comment>Changes accessories so bayonets never spawn on slot 1, only on slot 2, freeing up your weapon to have a second accessory. Does not despawn existing bayonets on slot 1.</comment>
				<comment>Does not affect certain weapons. Certain guns - mostly uniques and all pearls - now have a guaranteed accessory.</comment>
				<comment>WARNING: This mod alters the fundamental spawning rules of the game. Guns that spawn with a bayonet while this mod is active violate the sanity check. Do not deactivate this mod after using it. Please run this mod as early in your load order as possible.</comment>
				<comment>Coded with assistance from: the_Nocturni, LightChaosman</comment>
				<comment>Any mod that alters WeaponPartListCollectionDefinitions may be incompatible with this.</comment>
				<category name="Extended Description">
					<comment>Example Guns:</comment>
					<comment>Law (Now can have any accessory)</comment>
					<comment>Rubi and Grog Nozzle (Your choice of always has a blade or sometimes has a blade)</comment>
					<comment>Tattler (Now can have any accessory)</comment>
					<comment>Cobra (Always has an accessory)</comment>
					<comment>Pimpernel (Always has an accessory)</comment>
					<comment>Unforgiven (Always spawns with a bayonet)</comment>
				</category>

					<category name="Prefixes">
						<comment>Sets all assault rifle bayonet titles to minimal priority. If an assault rifle has two accessories, the title should not display the bayonet. This code is a workaround for bayonet titles taking priority over the primary accessory.</comment>
						<category name="Code">
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Weap_AssaultRifle.Name.Prefix_Dahl.Prefix_Bayonet_2 Priority 0.95</code>
							<code profiles="default">set GD_Weap_AssaultRifle.Name.Prefix_Bandit.Prefix_Bayonet_2 Priority 0.95</code>

					<category name="Prefixes">
						<comment>Sets all sniper rifle bayonet titles to minimal priority. If a sniper rifle has two accessories, the title should not display the bayonet. This code is a workaround for bayonet titles taking priority over the primary accessory.</comment>
						<category name="Code">

			<category name="Better Splatguns V1.4b by Orudeon">
				<comment>Alters Splatguns to have bonus projectiles, bonus velocity, bonus fire rate, no self-damage, and no gravity. This mod eliminates the spawn chance of Tech 2 (Critical) from all Splatguns due to it being useless.</comment>
				<comment>This mod is incompatible with Aaron0000's Splitters.</comment>
				<comment>Coded by Orudeon with major assistance from the_Nocturni.</comment>

			<category name="Shield Stat Tweaks V1.1 by Orudeon">
				<category name="Description">
					<comment>Tweaks shield parts to bring the average quality of randomly generated shields up. In designing this mod, several core tenets were adhered to...</comment>
					<comment>1) No brand should cripple your shield.</comment>
					<comment>2) Every brand should have something going for it.</comment>
					<comment>If an attribute was increased, it may have been increased a lot. If an attribute was decreased, it wasn't decreased by much. Excellent brands were already very close to the target 'quality'.</comment>
					<comment>Overall, shields should offer a little bit more tankiness and special effects should be stronger.</comment>
					<comment>By Orudeon, with assistance from SirUmnei, Zububu, AngrierPat, et al.</comment>
					<comment>Due to an as of yet unfixable bug, the Cracked Sash's inventory presentation is broken by this mod. This makes it impossible to determine its recharge rate and delay without guesswork. Its HUD capacity displays correctly.</comment>
				</category>

			<category name="Shield Behavior Overhaul V1.3 by Orudeon">
				<comment>Buffs most shield types (sometimes majorly) to improve overall usability and help specialized or common shields compete with generalized and unique-or-better ones.</comment>
				<comment>This mod is designed to be used with Shield Stat Tweaks.</comment>
				<comment>Thank you to LightChaosman (coded the Amp Shield behavior), AngrierPat (coded the Absorb shield data), zububu, et al.</comment>
				<comment>Changelog:</comment>
				<comment>V1.2b</comment>
				<comment>Big Boom Blaster no longer auto-pickup due to it overperforming.</comment>
				<comment>V1.2a</comment>
				<comment>No Delay Amp shields recharge rate lowered to 65% of normal rate (down from 70%). Now defaults to Standard Delay configuration.</comment>
				<comment>V1.2</comment>
				<comment>Give Booster shields additional functionality. They now have a one seventh chance to drop health or ammo and always drop two items.</comment>
				<comment>Add a workaround for No Delay amp shields. Use if you have drain-related issues, such as only draininng on the first shot.</comment>
				<comment>V1.1</comment>
				<comment>Vladof (Absorb) Shields tweaked</comment>
				<category name="Amp Shields">
					<comment>Redesigns common Amp Shields to constantly regenerate, apply Amp and drain every shot, and triples common Amp shield Amp damage to help them better compete with The Bee. Please thank LightChaosman for coding the Amp/Drain on every shot behavior.</comment>
					<comment>Includes optional code to make Amp shields constantly regenerate at the expense of slower regeneration.</comment>
					<code profiles="default">set GD_Shields.Skills.Impact_Shield_Skill:AttributeExpressionEvaluator_20 Expression (AttributeOperand1=ResourcePoolAttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.ShieldResourcePool.ShieldCurrentValue',ComparisonOperator=OPERATOR_GreaterThanOrEqual,Operand2Usage=OPERAND_PreferAttribute,AttributeOperand2=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Shield.ImpactShield_ConsumptionOnEmpower',ConstantOperand2=0.000000)</code>
					<hotfix name="ampshieldContinuousDrain" level="None">
						<code profiles="default">set GD_Shields.Skills.Impact_Shield_Skill:BehaviorProviderDefinition_0 BehaviorSequences[0].ConsolidatedLinkedVariables (0,0,1,0,2,1,0,1,1,0,0)</code>
					</hotfix>
					<code profiles="default">set GD_Shields.A_Item.Shield_Impact:AttributePresentationDefinition_0 Description Weapon shots deal bonus [skill]Amp Damage[-skill].</code>
					<category name="Delay Format (Defaults to normal)" MUT="true">

				<category name="Booster Shields">
					<comment>Shield Boosters now automatically pick up, giving you a periodic 'boost' to shield capacity with minimal interaction from the user, however their shield restore value is now 15% of capacity to balance this.</comment>
					<comment>Whiskey Tango Foxtrot now drops more boosters to increase its offensive capability.</comment>
					<comment>Additionally, common Booster shields have a 10% higher chance of dropping boosters and have a one seventh chance to drop health or ammo. Coded by AngrierPat for this mod.</comment>
					<comment>Pickup and boost amount data coded by the_Nocturni and used with permission.</comment>

			<category name="Relic Overhaul V1.1 by Orudeon">
				<comment>Redesigns most relics in the game to increase competitiveness and variability.</comment>
				<comment>Warning: Contains some presentation code that may alter how your existing relics or class mods display.</comment>
				<comment>Coded with assistance from LightChaosman, Mike/Soze, Jim Raven, Aaron0000,</comment>
				<comment>Dependencies coded by SirUmnei, used/altered with permission.</comment>
				<comment>Thank you to Mike for doing Relic appearances and fixing so many UI errors I don't know how to count them all.</comment>
				<category name="List Of Features">
					<comment>Massively buffs the statistics of Aggression relics to allow them to compete with similar relics.</comment>
					<comment>Dramatically increased the potency of Proficiency relics to compete with Bones of the Ancients.</comment>
					<comment>Redesigns the Might of the Seraphs to increase reload speed and fire rate with all weapons. Also increases movement speed. Requires UCP.</comment>
					<comment>Stockpile relics now add an absolute value of ammo, increasing usefulness at all points of gameplay. Additionally, all Stockpile relics now provide an enormous upgrade over Blood of the Ancients' ammo pools.</comment>
					<comment>Blood of the Ancients now add an absolute value of ammo. Additionally, all now provide more ammo than you could have gotten with a max quality percent-based one for a net upgrade to all ammo pools.</comment>
					<comment>Note: To get the final 'even' numbers, fractional bullets are granted at some upgrade levels. Your stockpile relic or Blood of the Ancients may grant unusual numbers below maximum quality.</comment>
					<comment>AngrierPat redesigned the Friendship Amulet to grant all team members (including yourself) +10% damage, maximum and minimum accuracy, weapon spread, reload speed, and magazine size, stacking with itself up to +40% to all stats.</comment>
					<comment>Increases the effectiveness of Elemental relics to allow them to compete with Bones of the Ancients.</comment>
					<comment>Changes Allegiance relics so blue and purple Allegiance relics often have all three attributes instead of two randomly selected ones.</comment>
					<comment>WARNING: Violates Sanity check. Probably deletes all existing Allegiance relics. Do not load affected save files without activating this mod first. Check included Gibbed codes.</comment>
					<comment>Increases the effectiveness of Protection relics to 71% shield capacity/recharge rate and adds 44.5% recharge delay at maximum quality to compete with Skin of the Ancients.</comment>
					<comment>Resistance relics now spawn with standardized resistance percents, now also grants resistance to dot elemental damage, and reduces your chance to be affected by dots (in addition to resisting impact damage).</comment>
					<comment>The Bone of the Ancients now comes in Explosive, Slag, and Melee/Melee Override Cooldown. Framework coded by SirUmnei and used/altered with permission.</comment>
					<comment>WARNING: Violates Sanity check. Deletes all existing Bones of the Ancients. Do not load affected save files without activating this mod first. Check included Gibbed codes.</comment>
					<comment>Skin of the Ancients now spawns with standardized resistance percents, now also grants resistance to dot elemental damage and reduces your chance to be affected by dots (in addition to resisting impact damage) and now always spawns with all three shield stats.</comment>
					<comment>WARNING: Violates Sanity check. Probably deletes all existing Skins of the Ancients. Do not load affected save files without activating this mod first.</comment>
					<comment>To adjust existing Skins of the Ancients, use Gibbed to change the BetaPart to Effect7. No other parts may have Effect7.</comment>
					<comment>Redesigns the Blood of the Seraphs to subtract a large portion of health in exchange for a very large chunk of constantly active health regeneration. Thank you to AngrierPat for the idea.</comment>
					<comment>Tenacity, Vitality, and Heart of the Ancients relics have optional vanilla-style changes or Aaron0000's Agility Relic designs incorporated.</comment>
				</category>
				<category name="Dependencies (Do not deactivate to preserve core functionality)">
